external affairs is a canadian television film , which aired on cbc television in 1999 . an adaptation of timothy findley 's play the stillborn lover , the film stars victor garber as henry raymond , a canadian diplomat in moscow who is summoned back to ottawa for questioning by michael &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; ( kenneth welsh ) , the minister of external affairs , after he is implicated in the murder of a young man . the investigation reveals secrets that threaten to destroy both men 's careers .